      "reading_romaji": "nomu",
      "translation": "to drink",
      "casual_usage": "In casual speech, のむ stays in its plain form — 「なにのむ？」(Nani nomu?) means 'What are you drinking?' and 「いっしょにのもう！」(Issho ni nomou!) means 'Let's drink together!' You'll hear this constantly at any get-together.",
