      "japanese": "きのう",
      "reading_romaji": "kinou",
      "translation": "yesterday",
      "casual_usage": "Use it to kick off any story about the day before — 「きのう、なにした？」(Kinō, nani shita?) means 'What did you do yesterday?' and rolls off the tongue naturally in any casual catch-up.",
      "formal_usage": "The word itself stays the same in formal settings; just pair it with polite verb endings. 「きのうはありがとうございました」(Kinō wa arigatō gozaimashita) is a perfectly polished way to thank someone for something that happened the previous day.",
